Boot from Ubuntu Server 12.04/14.04 LTS edition
F4 - select "Install a minimal system/virtual machine"
F6 - select "Expert Mode"
Language: English
Country:  Canada
Locales:  en_CA.UTF-8
Network:
	- IP Address, Netmask, Gateway, DNS Server
	- Host Name, Domain Name
Users:
	- Enable shadow passwords
	- Allow login as root
	- Don't create users
Timezone: America/Edmonton
Disk Partitioning:
	- create GPT partition table
	- /dev/sda2: /
	- /dev/sda3: /var
	- /dev/sda4: /tmp
	- /dev/sda5: swap
Software repositories: ca.archive.ubuntu.com
	- $release: main, restricted, universe, multiverse
	- $release-updates: main, restricted, universe, multiverse
	- $release-security: main, restricted, universe, multiverse
Software install: don't install any software
Boot loader: install GRUB to master boot record
Finish installation and boot into the new system
